{"type":"message","id":"263f9b02","parentId":"bccec2b1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:39:47.770Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-04-14 04:39 UTC] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/2). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Start ahv-dtlx-backend and test auth API.\n\n## Context\nBackend already built (dist/ folder exists). Repo at /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/\n\n## Steps\n1. cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend\n2. Start server: yarn start OR node dist/src/app.js (check package.json for correct start command)\n3. Wait for server to be ready (~5s)\n4. Test these endpoints with curl:\n   - POST /api/v1/auth/register (create test user)\n   - POST /api/v1/auth/login (login with test user)\n   - GET /api/v1/auth/profile (get profile with token)\n5. Report results\n\nUse exec tool for all commands. Use exec background=true for the server start, then curl to test.\n\nIf server fails to start, check error logs and try to fix. If MongoDB connection fails, that's ok - report what you found."}],"timestamp":1776141587558}}
