{"type":"message","id":"7ead78b3","parentId":"23d73815","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:42:58.195Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the app mounts `router` at `/api/v1`. The router mounts:\n1. `/auth` → auth.route (signin, change-password, refetch-token)\n2. `/guests` → guests.route\n3. `/devices` → devices.route\n4. authMiddleware.auth() - global auth middleware\n5. `/system` → system.routes (users, roles, user-role, agents, log-tasks)\n6. `/education` → education_routes\n7. `/operation` → operation_routes\n8. `/notification` → notification_routes\n\nThere is NO `/auth/register` endpoint. The endpoint the task asks me to test doesn't exist in the codebase.\n\n\nI need to reconsider what the actual API surface is. The auth routes have `/signin` for login, but there's no `/register` endpoint defined anywhere—the app doesn't have a user registration flow built in, so I should focus on testing what's actually available: the `/api/v1/auth/signin` endpoint and verify that the global auth middleware is properly protecting the routes that need it.\n\nLet me look at the swagger documentation to see what endpoints are actually exposed.","thinkingSignature":"a5c0d87f0c1e6b6c95382c6585b1cb32377d423958b08d6a2edea1375c5f4dbc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gojcq8lo05p2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/swagger.yaml | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":758,"output":288,"cacheRead":23513,"cacheWrite":979,"totalTokens":25538,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776141770579,"responseId":"062cf8ccebd208ae18125c23d3c457a5"}}
