{"type":"message","id":"4d078436","parentId":"e8c052cc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:44:53.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That's the problem! `jwt.sign` with `{id: undefined, ...}` does NOT include `id` in the token (it skips undefined values). So the token is created without the `id` field because `doc.id` is undefined for Mongoose lean docs (they have `_id` not `id`).\n\nThis is a BUG in the codebase. The `signToken` function uses `doc.id` but Mongoose lean docs use `doc._id` (or `doc._id.toString()`). \n\nBut I can't fix the codebase - I'm just testing. Let me work around this by checking if the `/users/me` endpoint has a way to authenticate without a valid token, or if there's another endpoint that works.\n \nActually, I realize the real issue: the token I'm using doesn't have an `id` field because `doc.id` was undefined when the token was signed, so the JWT strategy fails to verify it. To test the profile endpoint, I'd need to either fix the token generation or find an alternative approach.","thinkingSignature":"1eac589a378baee9eb0b21e0c59d2be70a01470b6b12dc079ccb5801fd7a1f13"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpg5nobw32n2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 20 \"getMe\\b\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/modules/users/users.controller.js 2>/dev/null || grep -rn \"getMe\\|getById\\b\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/dist/modules/users/users.controller.js | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":117,"output":323,"cacheRead":32237,"cacheWrite":839,"totalTokens":33516,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776141885549,"responseId":"062cf93eb81606c3a7bdb3ab191ea271"}}
